OL,3,CSubsidy card for gluten-free food
OL,4,Claunched in Wales
OL,6,FCabinet Secretary for Health and
OL,7,FSocial Care, Jeremy Miles said that
OL,8,Ffollowing a strict gluten-free diet is
OL,9,F"not a lifestyle choice but a medical
OL,10,Fnecessity" for those living with
OL,11,Fcoeliac disease.
OL,13,F"We want to de-medicalise the supply
OL,14,Fof gluten-free foods in Wales, giving
OL,15,Fpeople more freedom to access the food
OL,16,Fthey want to eat, more conveniently,
OL,17,Fto help them to manage their
OL,18,Fcondition," he added.
