OL,3,CSubsidy card for gluten-free food
OL,4,Claunched in Wales
OL,6,FCherylee Barker, who was diagnosed
OL,7,Fwith coeliac disease in 2007, was part
OL,8,Fof the pilot scheme and has been using
OL,9,Fthe card for six years.
OL,11,FShe said that, after being diagnosed,
OL,12,Fshe "quickly realised that maintaining
OL,13,Fa gluten-free diet would be costly,
OL,14,Fwith limited shopping options and hit-
OL,15,Fand-miss food choices."
OL,17,F"I jumped at the chance to join the
OL,18,Fpilot. I could try new products
OL,19,Fwithout feeling financially stretched
OL,20,Fand take back control of my diet," she
OL,21,Fsaid.
